<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.51/11–545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-05T17:00:00+02:00">November
                                    5, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 6—7:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>529. The Deputy Chief of the Economic Section of the Ministry of Foreign
                            Affairs has informed the Embassy in the strictest confidence that the
                            Zecho authorities intend to avail themselves of not more than 20 million
                            dollars of the proposed Export-Import Bank cotton credit as arrangements
                            have been made with the Soviet Govt to procure the balance of their
                            cotton requirements from the Soviet Union.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>